A car bomb attack at the Hilton hotel in Taba killed 23 Israelis and injured over 100 people of various nationalities.
The explosion, suspected to be orchestrated by Hamas, coincided with Jewish holidays.
Two more car bomb explosions targeted tourist camps in the Sinai desert, resulting in more casualties.
Despite warnings, many Israelis continued to vacation in the area.
Israeli officials suspected terrorism, while Egyptian authorities initially blamed gas leaks.
Evacuation efforts were underway for Israelis in the wake of the deadly attacks, urging them to leave Sinai immediately.
